{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Happiny}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=439|prev=Mime Jr.|nextnum=441|next=Chatot|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Happiny}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Happiny\n|jname=ピンプク\n|tmname=Pinpuku\n|ndex=440\n|sdex=096\n|adex=032\n|abrow=022\n|obrow=227\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Normal\n|category=Playhouse\n|height-ftin=2\'00"\n|height-m=0.6\n|weight-lbs=53.8\n|weight-kg=24.4\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Natural Cure\n|ability2=Serene Grace\n|abilityd=Friend Guard\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Undiscovered\n|eggcycles=40\n|evtotal=1\n|evhp=1\n|expyield=110\n|oldexp=255\n|lv100exp=800,000\n|gendercode=254\n|color=Pink\n|catchrate=130\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=happiny\n|generation=4\n|friendship=140\n}}\n\'\'\'Happiny\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ピンプク\'\'\' \'\'Pinpuku\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{pkmn2|baby}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Chansey}} when [[level]]ed up while holding an [[Oval Stone]] during the [[Time#Day|daytime]], which evolves into {{p|Blissey}} when leveled up with high [[friendship]].\n\n==Biology==\nHappiny is a small Pokémon that is shaped like an egg. It has a soft, smooth, light pink body. On top of its head is a curly outgrowth that resembles a {{wp|ponytail}}, with a dark pink band around the base. The appearance of this curly growth of hair often annoys Happiny. It has three round bumps on its forehead, and two pink circles on its cheeks. There is a pouch around the lower half of its body, which resembles a diaper. The pouch is red with a white stripe around the top.\n\nHappiny\'s pouch is rubbery and flexible, enabling the Happiny to put things into it with ease. As it cannot produce {{pkmn|Egg}}s yet, it makes up for it by carrying a white, Egg-shaped stone in its pouch to imitate {{p|Chansey}} and {{p|Blissey}}. It may give this stone to people whom it likes, and it has a habit of wandering around people\'s feet and causing them to stumble. Happiny is shown to be extremely strong in the {{pkmn|anime}}, as {{TP|Brock|one|Happiny}} has been seen lifting heavy things above its head. Happiny is a female-only species with no male counterpart.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Brock Happiny.png|thumb|left|220px|Happiny in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Happiny Egg.png|thumb|left|200px|A Happiny {{pkmn|Egg}} in the anime]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Brock\'s Happiny]]====\nHappiny debuted in \'\'[[DP038|One Big Happiny Family!]]\'\', hatching from {{an|Brock}}\'s {{pkmn|Egg}}. Unusually, in contrast to Happiny\'s extremely low {{DL|Statistic|Attack|Attack stat}} in the {{pkmn|games}}, she has amazing strength and can run with, pummel, and carry many heavy items and Pokémon for her size, such as having the ability to fling her {{pkmn|Trainer}} into the air with ease and carrying [[Ash\'s Grotle]] around in \'\'[[DP103|Jumping Rocket Ship!]]\'\'. She evolved into a Chansey in \'\'[[DP190|The Brockster Is In!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nTwo Trainers\' Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nFive Trainers\' Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\'.\n\nThree Trainers\' Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM017|Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!]]\'\'.\n\nThree Trainers\' Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM021|One Journey Ends, Another Begins...]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM023|Getting the Band Back Together!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM027|A Glaring Rivalry!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM050|Faba\'s Revenge!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM090|Securing the Future!]]\'\', where they joined the rest of [[Alola]] in showering {{DL|Light trio (anime)|Necrozma}} with light so it could return to its {{DL|List of Pokémon with form differences|Necrozma|true form}}.\n\nA Trainer\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[SM128|League Offenders and Defenders!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP038|Happiny|Ash\'s Pokédex|Happiny, the Playhouse Pokémon. It loves round white things. It carries a round stone in its pouch that looks like an {{pkmn|Egg}}, and gives it to people that it likes.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Happiny Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Happiny in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nHappiny debuted in a cameo in \'\'[[PS349|Passing by Probopass and Maneuvering around Magnezone]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Happiny appeared in \'\'[[PASM04|The Decision and the Tournament of Six]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Happiny (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=096|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of {{p|Chansey}}.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its belly pouch and gives the rock to its friends.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others\' feet and cause them to stumble.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It\'s bothered by how curly its hair looks.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others\' feet and cause them to stumble.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others\' feet and cause them to stumble.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It carries a round, egg-shaped rock i